  <bioghist id="aspace_725dd68abc735307d489f14fc8cbfe0b">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Professor of entomology, Cornell University.</p><p> Cornell University Class of 1896.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_ff0c6f7cb15eead76bc61bd6eea5c60b">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Scientific addresses; lecture notes on spiders; articles and bulletins; page proofs and original drawings and illustrations for <title>Insect Enemies of Shade Trees</title>; bibliographies; lists of students and alumni; scientific drawings and photographs; diaries; correspondence concerning the Cornell Department of Entomology; travel papers; personal accounts; newspaper clippings; outline talks and short manuscript writings on politics, education, the Cornell campus, and the Cornell Entomology Department; an oral history; photograph of Jugatae members; personal letters written to Glenn and Nannie Herrick; and genealogical material and family correspondence.</p><p> Includes a letter to Herrick from George Lincoln Burr with suggestions for the Comstocks of Cornell manuscript, written from Philadelphia, 12 April 1938.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_a1ad7c85cfe393616f5f4836de0bcde9">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Glenn Washington Herrick papers, #21-23-844. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
